
Installing Apache
-	Apache is being installed to run as the webserver, apache will deliver the website to the user when they access.
- Withoug apache there will not be anything returned to the user when they access the website.

- use the steps below to install apache
- execute the command

Sudo apt update

- sudo apt update is used as the currently installed apt repository may be out of date.

- Next, to download apache2 to the ubuntu instance use the command

Sudo apt install apache2 

- After this, your webserver should be accessible by searching the public ip address of the amazon ec2
